One of Luka Modric, Cristiano Ronaldo and Mohamed Salah will be named UEFA Men's Player of the Year on August 30. The winner will be named - along with the UEFA Women's Player of the Year and UEFA Champions League positional award winners – during the group stage draw in Monaco. The UEFA Europa League Player of the Season will be announced the following day. The rest of the top ten: 4 Antoine Griezmann (Atlético & France) – 72 points5 Lionel Messi (Barcelona & Argentina) – 55 points6 Kylian Mbappé (Paris & France) – 43 points7 Kevin De Bruyne (Manchester City & Belgium) – 28 points8 Raphaël Varane (Real Madrid & France) – 23 points9 Eden Hazard (Chelsea & Belgium) – 15 points10 Sergio Ramos (Real Madrid & Spain) – 12 points The award recognises the best players, irrespective of nationality, playing for a club within the territory of a UEFA member association during the past season. Players are judged on their performances in all competitions - domestic, continental and international. SOURCE: SPORT24